caption.text:
As I came to Thailand with no friend and family living near me, my circle of friendship went back to zero. ‚ñ´
‚ñ´
The reality of having some things in life going back to square one is never easy..especially when we've put so much effort to build it so far. ‚ñ´
‚ñ´
Building a quality circle of friendship will never be a piece of cake. Letting new people go inside my vulnerable parts is a risky challenge to take. ‚ñ´
‚ñ´
But leaving that zero to forever become zero is never wise. 
So here I am, challenging the challenges and the constraints back, and offering my heart along with its warmness as the new circle's base. ‚ñ´
‚ñ´
Some people may still find the warmness cold, the base wobbly, the builder crazy. 
I don't mind. I just need keep being the real Rosi..and, like Dori said, keep swimming in this new sea. 
#TheVeneziaThailand #TheVeneziaHuaHin #HuaHin #Chaam

caption.text:
I thought this Bandung trip was just a farewell before my Thailand journey. Turned out, it was a farewell for (almost) every single of us. üîπ
üîπ
I thought that having female best friends was impossible in my life until these 2 ladies happen. üîπ
üîπ
I don't know. I cannot explain. How they treat me and behave around me just feel right. üîπ
üîπ
There was a time when I was sitting at a corner, by myself, melancholy. I said nothing but they seemed to know what was happening inside me. 
Even when I was still pretty new in Thailand, I was shocked to know a call from them coming to my phone when I was about to burst into tears and no one was around. No. I didn't tell them. They did know the freaking right time. üîπ
üîπ
One of these ladies has a boyfriend. But she knows how to spare her time just to listen to my childish stories whenever I need. üîπ
üîπ
I was used to messing around them. I invaded their privacy. I farted in their their rooms many times. But they just let me be myself. And never do I feel I need to cover anything from them. üîπ
I am just never treated that way. üîπ
üîπ
I am beyond sad. But I am also super glad to know that she is going to enter a new stage of life. And another 'she' is soon to fly away to I don't know where and when. üîπ
üîπ
I am just Rosi and I never know you all can handle me this way. 
I hope meeting all of you one more time is not too much to ask later on October.

With love from Thailand, 
to my former colleagues, my English and life advisors, my older sisters, n my UNO rivals. 
Video is credited to @puansativa

caption.text:
Weekend is my most favorite moment here. That is the time for me to meet the crowd and to learn something new. Coz being a teacher will never ever ever stop you from being a student, right?

I have met plethora of Bangkok expats coming from many parts of the world, speaking English with various accents, and ranging from that millennia generation up to...baby boomers (no. kidding). On top of that. I have met plenty of God's creatures that appreciates me as Indonesian teaching English and also some others that tend to look down on me. Well, yeah. Thanks for the motivation.

These snaps are only from some of exciting meet ups I have joined so far. 
1st snap is my weekly English-Thai exchange class.

2nd snap is last week chilling and playing game event at Game Over Lounge. Well, if you are into games (board games, card game, console game) and happen to go places near BTS Thong Lo, go visit this cafe. This cafe has international atmosphere since you can find a lot of foreigners here.

3rd snap is last week Urban Challenger meet up. We, young BKK expats, had a wonderful (and of course affordable) lunch at Pier 21 of Terminal 21 mall. This food court is so amazing that you can buy any street food sold in a mall. How affordable is the food? Oh well, who can say no to 15 baht for 2 scoops of delicious ice cream, 15 baht for a glass of grape juice, to 40 baht for a bowl of fish ball, and to a clean and cool place to eat?

Last but not least, the last snap is a picture of our trainer in self-development class. What does 'our' refer to? Of course, Thai people and expats folk (again). We mingle together to set a goal to achieve within 12 months time and figure out how to achieve that.

BKK adlh kota yg menjawab kerinduanku pada Jakarta. The dynamic life here, the fast-paced life, the people who always wants to learn really energize me. 
To close my speech *eh photo caption, lemme introduce myself as an Indonesian who chooses English teaching as her career. 
Discriminate me and keep looking down on me until one day I make ur jaw drop of what this NNES can do. *mic drop

PS: sorry focus captionnya macam2

The next album is about this weekend Thai Dinner with Bangkok Expats. üîΩ
üîΩ 
I am on cloud 9 to find this meet up. Thanks to Chef Jekky, a Thai Chef, for holding this weekly Thai dinner for us, Thailand Expats, who are craving for delicious and absolutely healthy Thai food. üî∏
üî∏
While enjoying the traditionally cooked dishes, we can always chat with many expats from various countries.. from many continents even. üîΩ
üîΩ 
Beyond fun. Beyond happy. Rosi and her tummy are looking forward to tasting another food from ur magical hands, chef! üòäüòäüíï

üîπ

üîπ

üîπ
I now know the key of unlocking the self-love. 
I need to keep running.. To take the extra miles. . . 
I get that great feeling once my feet land on the finish line. 
That love to myself is now back to be mine. 
Then? 
You know? What you feel inside shines to the outside. 
The love is now my inside out might. üîπ
üîπ
üîπ 
Now, 3-5km is my menu, almost everyday. 
Strength and endurance trainings are another ingredients I add amid them twice a week, to make the running 'more delicious'. And the dynamic rest.. Yoga... I schedule it in the middle of those rehearsals. üîπ

Keep smiling! 
Keep moving! 
Keep running! 
And keep loving! üî∏

caption.text:
Sanata Dharma University.

I firstly fell in love with this university when I joined an event held by its English Education Department, namely English Action Day 2011.
First day for the elimination round. Second day for the final round.
Only in those two days, when it came to free time during the event, I found myself pondering about being its student one year after that day.

Dunno. I got excited with, interested in, and curious about the atmosphere this university offers. It felt like the atmosphere would cater me back with something I've missed and lost for a long time.

Freshmen. Sophomore. Third and fourth year student.
I think that I now know what the atmosphere would like to provide me with.
It is a place where minds and heart are educated at once to become fully human.
Yeah, fully human. The education consists of mind and heart. "Excellent and Humanistic". It is the spirit infusing its both academic and non academic activities.

Thank you for this almost 4 years, dear SDU!
Thank you for transmogrifying both my mind and heart. Thank you especially for bringing along compassion and conscience beside competence in my college study.
Thank you for those tons of learning opportunities that have transformed me into Rosi who I love more than Rosi in 4 years ago.

Eventually, better late than never.
I'd like to congratulate you for making your mark as the best private university in Yogyakarta and the second best in Indonesia. Love! ‚ù§ üéì

Jakarta -¬†Menguasai bahasa Inggris bisa menjadi investasi di masa depan. Dengan hadirnya Masyarakat Ekonomi ASEAN (MEA), kalangan pekerja dituntut memiliki kemampuan bahasa asing khususnya bahasa Inggris yang baik.

Mempelajari bahasa Inggris tentu perlu dilakukan sejak dini. Dalam hal ini, guru bahasa Inggris memiliki peran penting untuk menumbuhkan kecintaan siswa terhadap mata pelajaran tersebut.

Sebagai seorang guru bahasa Inggris, Maria Dewi Rosari, berusaha sebaik mengemas materi agar bisa mewadahi beragamnya tipe belajar siswa. "Dalam satu kelas, pasti ada siswa yang lebih suka belajar dengan mendengarkan (audio), melihat sesuatu (visual), atau dengan bergerak (kinestetik). Dalam hal ini, guru harus mampu memposisikan diri sebagai teman belajar, bukan sebagai pengajar," ujar gadis yang akrab disapa Rosi ini.

Selain itu, kata dia, seorang guru juga harus mampu membuat variasi kegiatan pembelajaran agar menjadi menarik bagi siswa. Misalnya, kata Rosi, dengan menggunakan berbagai macam permainan baik di dalam maupun di luar kelas. "Seorang guru juga dituntut untuk mampuup-to-date¬†informasi terkini, agar ketika mengajar dirinya tidak hanya mengajarkan bahasa tetapi juga pengetahuan baru, terutama yang menyangkut nilai-nilai moral," tambah Rosi.

caption.text:
I still remember the time when I asked for a help from a friend of mine. I asked him what was the meaning of this and that. It's about my assignments.
Instead of being happy, I was annoyed with his not answering directly what I was asking. He kept questioning me, and as the questions went from one to another, they became deeper.
"U r wasting my time" - I thought
Yet, suddenly, he said "You already get the answer. Ur assignment is done." And he kept doing that again and again whenever I came with a question.
As the time goes by, I realized that I had to be thankful for being treated like that. Being questioned for many times instead of being given the answers directly means he was training me (and my mind). Fortunately, he was doubling the help I was asking.
And when I said "thank you", he answered "I did nothing".
Oh.. I just found a real figure of teacher :)
#teacher #goodteacher #realteacher #teaching #teachingquote

caption.text:
Bunches of people around me ask me why I am still single.. some of which even suprisedly ask me why I go here and there alone, without someone escorting or accompanying me.
Well, as long as that "one" has not come yet, why am I supposed to hurry?
Maybe I have not yet learned the most important thing like managing my time between for my own affairs and for my family.
Maybe there are still bunches of new places, new acquaitances, new activities, new lessonsss are better to be learned when we are single.
So, if you are single right now, why should hurry? Why should worry?
God's time is always perfect!
One is created for another.
Mocking person who is still single is a waste of time.
Letting ourselves be trapped in that mocking is the another one.
